OL,3,CLondoners wake up to 'the first taste
OL,4,Cof winter' as snows falls on the
OL,5,Ccapital.
OL,7,FColder temperatures can be difficult
OL,8,Ffor a person with dementia to adjust
OL,9,Fto, and they may not always be able to
OL,10,Fcommunicate that they are cold ` or
OL,11,Fthey may not even recognise it
OL,12,Fthemselves," the charity said.
OL,14,FIt advised the public to check in on
OL,15,Floved ones, friends and neighbours
OL,16,Fliving with the condition.
