OL,3,CLondoners wake up to 'the first taste
OL,4,Cof winter' as snows falls on the
OL,5,Ccapital.
OL,7,FMs Abrahams said it is "vital" older
OL,8,Fpeople stay "fit, warm and well if
OL,9,Fthey can" by having hot food and
OL,10,Fdrinks throughout the day, wrapping up
OL,11,Fwarm and sleeping with the windows
OL,12,Fclosed.
OL,14,FThe change in weather has also
OL,15,Fdisrupted thousands of train
OL,16,Fpassengers.
OL,18,FBy 11am on Tuesday, 37% London North
OL,19,FEastern Railway had been disturbed and
OL,20,Facross the country many other lines
OL,21,Fhave been affected.
